ws/2002/dec/04/guardianobituaries|last=Roth|first=Andrew|title=Lord Emslie|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2002-12-03|accessdate=2019-04-09}}</ref>\n*[[Arturo Guzman Decena]] founder of [[Los Zetas]].\n*[[J. Roger Pichette]], 81, Canadian politician.\n*[[Prince Takamado]], 47, Japanese prince.\n\n===22===\n*[[Parley Baer]], 88, American radio, television and film actor (''[[The Andy Griffith Show]]'', ''[[The Adventures of Ozzie and Harriet]]'', ''[[The Addams Family (1964 TV series)|The Addams Family]]'', ''[[Dave (film)|Dave]]'').<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2002/nov/24/local/me-baer24|last=Oliver|first=Myrna|title=Parley Baer, 88; 64-Year Career Spanned Radio, TV, Movies|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2002-11-24|accessdate=2019-03-12}}</ref>\n*[[Joan Barclay]], 88, American actress.\n*[[Norman Clarke (physicist)|Norman Clarke]], 86, British physicist and politician.\n*[[Christine Marion Fraser]], 64, Scottish novelist.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/obituaries/christine-marion-fraser-1-630800|title=Christine Marion Fraser|work=[[The Scotsman]]|date=2002-11-27|accessdate=2019-04-19}}</ref>\n*[[Arne Melln\u00e4s]], 69, Swedish composer.\n\n===23===\n*[[Erna Bogen-Bog\u00e1ti]], 95, Hungarian Olympic fencer ([[Fencing at the 1928 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's foil|1928 women's foil]], [[Fencing at the 1932 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's foil|1932 bronze medal women's foil]], [[Fencing at the 1936 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's foil|1936 women's foil]]).<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20161202231525/https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/erna-bogen-bogati-1.html Erna Bogen-Bog\u00e1ti, Sports-Reference / Olympic Sports]. Retrieved 2019-03-16.</ref>\n*[[Boudewijn B\u00fcch]], 53, Dutch writer, poet and television presenter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/boudewijn-buumlch-5359812.html|last=Blom|first=Philipp|title=Boudewijn B\u00fcch|work=[[The Independent]], London|date=2002-12-23